Sri Lanka Clears Colombo Development Project on World Bank Loan

-- B y   A n u s h a   O n d a a t j i e
-- 
2011-05-26T11:32:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-26/sri-lanka-clears-colombo-development-project-on-world-bank-loan.html
Sri Lanka ’s cabinet approved a
project to develop the infrastructure of the capital city
 Colombo  with a $150 million loan from the  World Bank , the
island’s information department said on its website today.  The project, that will help reduce flooding in the city,
will begin at the end of this year and will complete in three
years, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anusha Ondaatjie in Colombo at 
 anushao@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
